  class:container
  widgets
    div
      class:row
      widgets
        div
          class:col-25
          widgets
            p
              class:rounded shaded bg air-inner
              innerValue:This column use the 'col-25' class, which means it will use 25% of the available space.
        div
          class:col-50 offset-25
          widgets
            p
              class:rounded shaded bg air-inner
              innerValue:@"While this will use 'col-50'and 'offset-25', which means it will be moved forward by 25% of the available space."


/*
 * Forms elements
 */
create-widget
  class:container
  widgets
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            h3
              innerValue:Form elements
            p
              innerValue:@"Below you can find the most commonly used form elements."
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            button
              innerValue:Button
            button
              innerValue:@"Icon button <span class=""icon-trash""></span>"
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input:chk-1
              type:checkbox
              checked
            label
              for:chk-1
              innerValue:Checkbox
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input:rdo-1
              type:radio
              name:rdo-group-1
            label
              for:rdo-1
              innerValue:Radio button 1
            input:rdo-2
              type:radio
              checked
              name:rdo-group-1
            label
              for:rdo-2
              innerValue:Radio button 2
            input:rdo-3
              type:radio
              name:rdo-group-1
            label
              for:rdo-3
              innerValue:Radio button 3
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            select
              widgets
                option
                  name:opt-1
                  innerValue:option 1
                option
                  name:opt-2
                  innerValue:option 2
                  selected
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input
              type:text
              placeholder:Text input ...
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            literal
              element:textarea
              placeholder:Textarea input ...
              rows:5
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            h3
              innerValue:Sizing
            p
              innerValue:Most form elements can also be explicitly given a size, through 'wider' and 'smaller' CSS classes.
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input
              type:text
              class:smaller
              placeholder:Smaller text input ...
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input
              type:text
              placeholder:Default text input ...
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input
              type:text
              class:wider
              placeholder:Wider text input ...
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            p
              innerValue:@"You can also make a form control fill the entire column, by adding the 'fill' class to it. Below is a 'col-80 
offset-10' column with a textarea inside of it."
        div
          class:col-80 offset-10
          widgets
            literal
              element:textarea
              rows:7
              class:fill
              placeholder:This textarea has the 'fill' class ...
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            h3
              innerValue:Strips
            p
              innerValue:@"You can also create 'strips' of related form elements, by making sure the container element of your form elements
has the 'strip' class."
        div
          class:col-100 strip
          widgets
            label
              innerValue:Info
              for:txt-strip-1
            input:txt-strip-1
              class:smaller
              type:text
              placeholder:Strip textbox ...
            select
              class:smaller
              widgets
                option
                  innerValue:Option 1
                option
                  innerValue:Option 2
            button
              innerValue:OK
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            p
              innerValue:@"If you add a label inside of your strips, like we did above, it will appear similarly to the rest of your strip.
Notice, if you wish to add a checkbox or a radio button inside your strips, you should wrap them in a 'span' element, like the following illustrates."
        div
          class:col-100 strip
          widgets
            label
              for:chk-strip-1
              innerValue:Checkbox
            span
              widgets
                input:chk-strip-1
                  type:checkbox
                  checked
            input
              class:smaller
              type:text
              placeholder:Textbox ...
            button
              innerValue:OK
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            h3
              innerValue:Fullwidth strips
            p
              innerValue:@"You can also combine 'strip' width 'fill' on the container element, if you have a select or textbox widget inside of 
your strip, like the following illustrates. If you do, the strip as a whole will fill the entire width, whatever that is, which can be controlled 
on the container by using one of the 'col-x' classes. This gives you fine grained control over the width of your strips, making them easily
fill the entire width of their parent elements."
        div
          class:col-40 strip fill
          widgets
            label
              for:txt-strip-fill-1
              innerValue:Text box 1
            input:txt-strip-fill-1
              type:text
              placeholder:Textbox ...
        div
          class:col-60 strip fill
          widgets
            label
              for:select-strip-fill-1
              innerValue:Select
            select:select-strip-fill-1
              widgets
                option
                  innerValue:Foo
                option
                  innerValue:Bar
            button
              innerValue:OK
        div
          class:col-70 strip fill
          widgets
            label
              for:txt-strip-fill-2
              innerValue:Text box 2
            input:txt-strip-fill-2
              type:text
              placeholder:Textbox ...


/*
 * Misc. classes.
 */
create-widget
  class:container
  widgets
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            h3
              innerValue:Misc. classes
            p
              innerValue:@"There exists some contextual classes, allowing you to add some visual clues to your widgets. Below you can
find some examples of combinations of some of these classes."
        div
          class:col-50
          widgets
            div
              class:bg air-inner rounded shaded
              widgets
                p
                  innerValue:Classes 'bg air-inner rounded shaded'
        div
          class:col-50
          widgets
            div
              class:air-inner emphasized
              widgets
                p
                  innerValue:Classes 'air-inner emphasized'
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-50
          widgets
            div
              class:air-inner warning
              widgets
                p
                  innerValue:Classes 'air-inner warning'
        div
          class:col-50
          widgets
            div
              class:air-inner success
              widgets
                p
                  innerValue:Classes 'air-inner success'
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            p
              innerValue:@"The 'bg' class is contextual to your skin, and normally adds some repeating pattern, that relates to your skin somehow.
The 'warning', 'success' and 'emphasized' classes, are normally red, green, and the main color of your skin."
            p
              innerValue:@"Notice, the last 'col' inside of a 'row' has its right padding removed, to make sure it fills the entire viewport.
This means you must sometimes add another 'row' in between 'col' elements that wraps unto a new line. In general, you should have one row for
each sum of 'col' elements that adds up to 100."
    div
      class:row air-top
      widgets
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            input
              class:error fill
              placeholder:Input element with 'error' class ...
            select
              class:error fill
              widgets
                option
                  innerValue:Select with 'error' class ...
                option
                  innerValue:Some other option
            literal
              element:textarea
              class:error fill
              rows:5
              placeholder:Textarea element with 'error' class ...
            input:some-error-checkbox
              type:checkbox
              class:error
            label
              innerValue:Some checkbox with 'error'
              for:some-error-checkbox
        div
          class:col-100
          widgets
            p
              innerValue:@"Above is some example of adding the 'error' class to your form elements. You can set multiple form elements into
an 'error' mode, by adding the error class to its parent container. An 'error' element, will have some red borders, signifying that the input
contains some sort of error."


